I rise to the world of light, with my deities whom I have served!'
he murmured;
'the brightness of their presence is like a flaming fire; the smoke of their breath pours forth around me like the smoke of incense!

"Yes,"
said Mick;
"I don't think I could get through the day, if it wurno' for our Institute."

And, perhaps, not quite awake to what he did, but
                  attracted like a child to a candle, at last he proceeded from staring to touching;
                  he put out his hand and stroked one curl, as gently as if it were a bird.
